<TITLE> Ctg police officials arrested on charges of robbery remanded </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Chittagong, Feb 11, (bdnews24.com) - A Chittagong court Monday allowed interrogators two days to quiz three police officials who were arrested on charges of robbery. Security officials arrested the officials early Monday from the office of an assistant commissioner in Panchlaish thana. The detainees include assistant police commissioner Abu Saleh Mohammad Mofazzal Huq, constable Ehsanul Islam and constable Mohammad Abdur Rouf, said Kotwali police station sub inspector Syed Faruk Ahmed. Metropolitan magistrate Abdur Rouf granted two days after investigator Abul Hossain prayed for a five-day remand for interrogation. Faruk said the charges involved robbery at the house of businessman Faruk Ahmed Chowdhury in the city's Mehedibag area. The businessman alleged that the accused took part in the robbery and looted gold and cash. Chittagong Metropolitan Police commissioner M Akbar Ali said the detainees admitted that they were involved with the robbery. bdnews2
